  "text": "Turn the volume all the way up! Round of 16, 7 July 2026 — and Belgium ended the USA's home World Cup with a clinical, four-goal display. The hosts dreamed of a deep run in front of their own fans; Belgium's golden-tinged generation had other ideas.\n\n9' — Charles De Ketelaere buried it, 0–1! 31' — Malik Tillman lashed it home, 1–1! 33' — Charles De Ketelaere made no mistake, 1–2! 57' — Hans Vanaken found the net, 1–3! 93' — Romelu Lukaku smashed it in, 1–4!\n\nCharles De Ketelaere's first-half double did the early damage, either side of Malik Tillman's fine reply for the hosts. For a moment, at 2-1, the American crowd believed a comeback was on. Hans Vanaken's composed finish and a late Romelu Lukaku strike snuffed that out and made the scoreline emphatic. Belgium looked ruthless and experienced — the profile of a side that intends to be around in the final week.\n\nYou could feel the tension crackle around the ground with every attack.\n\nThis is knockout football at its rawest — win, or fly home.\n\nThe neutrals were on their feet; nobody in the building sat still.\n\nGolden Boot, glory, the lot — it was all on the line out there.\n\nFULL-TIME: USA 1–4 Belgium! Belgium march on, USA head home heartbroken — and here's the beautiful part: every goal, every minute you just heard is locked on-chain and verified by TxLINE. No hot air, no guesswork, just receipts. What. A. Game!",
